The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Honda mulls second facility
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Honda mulls second facility
          A STAFF REPORTER                      Sushil K. Kabra in Calcutta on Friday. A Telegraph picture                          
	Calcutta, Feb. 12: Honda Motorcycle amp; Scooter India (HMSI), a wholly owned unit of Japans Honda Motor Corp, is planning to set up a second facility to expand capacity.        
	We will reach 100 per cent utilisation next year. We are doing an internal study on a second plant, operating head (finance and accounts) Sushil K. Kabra said after launching the 110cc CB Twister here today.        
	According to sources, the company would require at least 50 acres for the assembly unit and need to invest at least Rs 400 crore in the first phase.        
	At present, the company has capacity to make 1.5 million scooters and motorcycles in India.         
	It is growing at 20 per cent per annum, and India is the second largest market for the company after China.        
	HMSI expects to sell 1.25 million scooters and bikes in this fiscal and 1.5 million units during the next.         
	The company enjoys a 13 per cent market share in India, while Hero Honda Motors  another affiliate of the Japanese parent  dominates with sales expected to exceed 4 million this fiscal.                                                                                                                                       
